snippet: Citing international and Afghan election observers, the nation’s complaints commission said this weekend’s vote was much cleaner than the one in 2009.
abstract: Afghanistan's Independent Election Complaints Commission reports a cleaner presidential election this year than widely discredited 2009 election; none of leading candidates have said so far that they would dispute this year's balloting, whose results have not yet been announced.

byline.original: By ROD NORDLAND and MATTHEW ROSENBERG
byline.contributor: Habib Zahori and Jawad Sukhanyar contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Citing international and Afghan election observers, the nation’s complaints commission said this weekend’s vote was much cleaner than the one in 2009.

headline.main: After ’09 Fraud, Afghanistan Reports a Cleaner Election
headline.print_headline: After ’09 Fraud, Afghanistan Reports a Cleaner Election
